✅ 3 biseries de sentadilla a 1 pierna x 15 repeticiones + femoral sentada x 10 repeticiones.
✅ 3 biseries de tijera a 1 pierna x 10 repeticiones + prensa a 1 pierna x 15 repeticiones.

node.text:
PLEASE HELP US BY DONATING AND SHARING

You can donate in the site GO FUND ME:

https://www.gofundme.com/f/pkhwn7-my-moms-cancer-treatment ( LINK IN MY BIO )

Information Contact in USA: 
+17065259823 Christian Morales
Instagram @christianmoralesc

My mom, Karen Castillo, was diagnosed with colon cancer back in April of this year. She has had a big surgery where part of her colon was removed along with 13 lymph nodes where cancer had already spread. For this reason and the size of the tumor in her colon, her cancer is considered stage 3B.
After everything was removed from her body and recovered from surgery, doctors recommended an extensive treatment of chemotherapy to eliminate all possible cancer cells left in the body. Without a doubt, my mom put herself through this treatment, but after only three sessions, her body was not taking it well. The side effects of chemotherapy were extremely severe, to the point where she could not walk and was deteriorating the rest of her vital organs. After seeing how her body was taking chemotherapy, how she could not be a functional human being, and the doctors giving her a very low success rate, she decided to stop and look for other options.

This is how we found an alternative treatment that she started right away and kept for about four months.  At first, we thought that the treatment was working well, but blood tests said the opposite after a couple of months. Her tests, which show tumor levels in her body, were increasing slowly until, just like millions of people, my mom was infected with Covid-19, which made her immune system weak, giving the cancer cells the possibility to take over and multiply exponentially. After the two weeks of quarantine, her cancer markers indicated an increase of more than twice what it was before, and it keeps growing every day that goes by.

My mom's current treatment is not strong enough to eliminate her advanced cancer, and it is also very expensive. She needs to switch to a stronger treatment that stops cancer cells from multiplying and attacks them directly using a combination of advanced techniques which would give my mom a better chance of surviva
